comments: Allen (MEM) strips the ball from Asik (NOP) immediately after he gathers the rebound.
Young (IND) makes incidental contact with Saric (PHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
Young (IND) and Ilyasova (PHI) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Young (IND) and Kanter (OKC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Young (IND) and Adams (OKC) briefly engage and separate during rebounding.
Young (IND) maintains legal guarding position and Plumlee (POR) loses control of the ball.
Aminu (POR) makes marginal contact with Hill (SAC) that does not affect his SQBR.
Muscala (ATL) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically as he contests Simmons' (ORL) driving shot attempt.
Ulis (PHX) maintains legal guarding position on Evans' (MEM) driving shot attempt.
Chandler (PHX) legally touches the ball above the cylinder on the inbound pass. Goaltending rules do not apply because he
Williams Jr. (MIA) sets the screen on Payton (ORL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Wiggins (MIN) legally contests Williams' (LAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered
Randolph (SAC) and Whiteside (MIA) make incidental contact with each other during rebounding.
Evans (MEM) makes contact to Griffin's (DET) arm during the rip-through and affects his SQBR.
Evans (MEM) makes marginal contact with Tolliver (DET) during rebounding.
Biyombo (ORL) sets the screen on Bembry (ATL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Barton (DEN) makes incidental contact with Williams (LAC).
Tolliver (DET) makes incidental contact with Matthews (DAL) during rebounding.
Baldwin IV (POR) makes incidental contact with Murray (DEN) during his shot attempt.
Dudley (BKN) commits a take foul on Jackson (DET).
Hayward (BOS) cleanly dislodges the ball from Williams (BOS) during the inbound.
Kleber (DAL) is vertical and in a legal guarding position in the RA.
Smith Jr. (NYK) and Clarkson (CLE) make incidental contact with one another during the loose ball.
Brogdon (IND) does not deliver contact to Martin (CHA) as he makes the step back move.
Martin (CHA) brings his hand to Brogdon's (IND) side momentarily and removes it without affecting his SQBR.
Trier (NYK) makes marginal contact with Russell (GSW) during the inbound and doesn't affect his FOM.
Green (GSW) makes clean contact with the ball during Trier's (NYK) drive.
VanVleet (TOR) and Bledsoe (NOP) briefly engage and disengage off ball.
McDaniels (MIN) makes incidental contact with Hayward's (CHA) right arm as they each attempt to retrieve the rebound.

Antetokounmpo (MIL) extends his left arm outward and some contact occurs with Quickley's (NYK) head/neck area as Quickley is cutting. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bey (DET) gathers the ball on his right foot, then legally steps with his left foot, establishing his left foot as his pivot foot.
Booker (PHX) briefly grasps Garland's (CLE) arm during the screen and does not affect his FOM.
Brown Jr. (OKC) legally contests Ferrell's (LAC) driving shot attempt.
Paul (PHX) does not bring part of his hand under the ball when he brings his dribble to a pause.
Curry (PHI) moves laterally defending Young's (ATL) drive and marginal contact occurs.
Porter Jr. (GSW) attempts to steal the ball and marginal contact occurs with Campazzo's (DEN) side, which does not affect his SQBR.
Valanciunas (NOP) establishes his screening position in Garland's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact.
Green (DEN) and Lyles (DET) briefly engage and disengage while rebounding.
Green (DEN) moves laterally against Cunningham's (DET) path and makes incidental foot to ball contact during his drive to the basket.
Mitchell (UTA) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Johnson (SAS) prior to incidental arm and body contact taking place.
